history.content: I mistakenly enrolled in a Summer 2019 course while trying to quickly enroll in a course for Fall 2019. I dropped the course immediately after by submitting a withdrawal form and am now left with a $100 summer session cancellation fee. It is ridiculous how easy it is to make this mistake (e.g. pressing a key when selecting term), and there should be some separate registration for summer sessions or an additional confirmation message about fees during enrollment. I already emailed Summer Sessions and Cal Student Central Billing about the issue but am expecting some generic reply after waiting forever about how the fee is non-refundable. Any suggestions on how I can get this fee waived? Anyone have experience getting it or similar fees waived?
history.subject: Summer Session Cancellation Fee
